    "Name": "Argus",
    "Details": "<color=#F79B26>The Argus, a 60-ton BattleMech developed by Achernar BattleMechs and Robinson Standard BattleWorks, was initially an OmniMech but later resubmitted as a BattleMech that was quickly picked up by the AFFC.</color>\n\nUsing the most advanced technology available to the Federated Commonwealth, the Argus 4D carries a Rotary Autocannon/5 capable of firing at up to six times the normal rate of a standard autocannon, making it highly destructive at close range. This is complemented by two ER Medium Lasers, and a single  Machine Gun for defense against unarmored infantry attacks. It also has a LRM-10 launcher, which provides the Argus with some long range striking capabilities. All direct-fire weapons are linked to an advanced Targeting Computer, making them extremely accurate.\n",
